{
  "texts": [
    "This setting accommodates features with light-tailed distributions, including bounded or discrete categorical features.",
    "A formal statement is given in Theorem 4.Theorem 3.",
    "We assume that unwatermarked tabular data X has rows x i i.i.d.∼ N (0, Σ), where Σ ∈ R p×p is positivedefinite.",
    "Denote the smallest and largest eigenvalue of Σ by λ min and λ max, respectively.",
    "Define N α,β (γ, δ, σ) as the number of rows required for the Gaussian noise-corrupted table X wm +ε to achieve a statistical test with power 1-β at significance level α, where X wm denote the table watermarked under soft hyperparameters (γ, δ) and ε i,j i.i.d.∼ N (0, σ 2)."
  ]
}